{{Refimprove|date=September 2010}} [[File:NASA High Flyers Alphabet Activity Book.pdf|thumb|Example of an activity book. ]] An '''activity book''' is a type of [[book]], generally aimed at [[children]], which contains [[interactive]] content such as [[game]]s, [[puzzles]], [[quiz]]zes, pictures to colour and other elements which involve [[writing]] or [[drawing]] in the book itself. The book may, or may not, have a loose [[narrative]] or contain other non-interactive elements structured around the interactive elements. Activity books may be made for [[entertainment]], [[education]] or a mixture of both.
Specific types of activity books include [[colouring book]]s and [[puzzle book]]s. A book is normally referred to as an activity book if it combines a variety of interactive elements and does not fall neatly into one of these more specific categories.
== Examples == Activity books are typically centred around a particular theme. This may be a generic theme, e.g. dinosaurs, or based on a toy, television show, book, or game.
For example, the [[Where's Wally?]] series of books (known as Where's Waldo? in the USA) by [[Martin Handford]] consists of both [[Puzzle book|puzzle books]], wherein the reader must search for characters hidden in pictures, and activity books such as ''[[Where's Waldo?: The Ultimate Fun Book]]'', which include a wider range of games and activities as well as puzzles. In 2018, [[Nintendo]] announced its intention to publish activity books based on its trademarked characters and games.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.digitaltrends.com/gaming/nintendo-childrens-activity-books-random-house/|title=Who says print is dead? Nintendo turns its attention to kids’ activity books|date=2018-05-04|work=Digital Trends|access-date=2018-06-02|language=en-US}}</ref> Other franchises for which a number of activity books are available include:
* Books by [[Julia Donaldson]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=|title=Superworm Sticker Activity Book|last=Donaldson|first=Julia|date=2018-05-03|publisher=Alison Green Books|others=Axel Scheffler|year=|isbn=9781407184647|location=|pages=|language=English}}</ref> * [[Diary of a Wimpy Kid (book series)|Diary of a Wimpy Kid]] series by [[Jeff Kinney (writer)|Jeff Kinney]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=|title=Diary of a Wimpy Kid: Do-It-Yourself Book|last=Kinney|first=Jeff|date=2011-06-09|publisher=Puffin|year=|isbn=9780141339665|edition=1st|location=London|pages=|language=English}}</ref> * [[Lego|LEGO]]<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url=|title=THE LEGO® BATMAN MOVIE: Choose Your Super Hero Doodle Activity Book|last=|first=|date=2017-01-12|publisher=Egmont|year=|isbn=9781405286251|edition=UK|location=|pages=|language=English}}</ref> * [[DC Comics]]<ref name=":0" /> * [[Marvel Comics|Marvel]]<ref>{{Cite book|title=Marvel The Avengers Ultimate Factivity Collection|last=|first=|date=2015-03-02|publisher=DK Children|year=|isbn=9780241007587|edition=1st|location=|pages=|language=English}}</ref> * [[CBeebies|Cbeebies]] television shows, e.g. [[The Adventures of Abney & Teal|Abney and Teal]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=|title=The Adventures of Abney & Teal: Busy Days Sticker Activity Book|last=|first=|date=2014-08-07|publisher=Walker Entertainment|year=|isbn=9781406356571|location=|pages=|language=English}}</ref> * [[Horrible Histories]] series by Terry Deary<ref>[http://www5.scholastic.co.uk/zone/book_horr-histories-activity.htm Scholastic Children's Books: Horrible Histories]</ref>
